Articulate investment thesis aligned with innovation potential

7. Risk Management and Mitigation

Identify potential disruptive risks
Develop adaptive response scenarios
Create resilient strategic frameworks
Minimize potential failure points
Apply root cause-centered problem diagnosis
Build learning systems through failure
Implement results-focused continuous evolution processes
Conduct comprehensive risk assessment with mitigation strategies

8. 5-Step Reality-Based Innovation Process

Step 1: Set Innovative Goals - Create clear objectives for market creation and fundamental problem solving
Step 2: Identify Market Barriers - Accurately diagnose current market limitations and challenges
Step 3: Diagnose Root Causes - Identify underlying causes rather than surface-level problems
Step 4: Design Innovative Plans - Create 10x better solutions with sustainable competitive advantages
Step 5: Implement with Measurement - Execute with clear metrics and rapid feedback loops

9. Marketing and Customer Acquisition Strategy

Develop comprehensive go-to-market strategies
Design innovative marketing channels aligned with target customers
Create content and communication strategies that articulate unique value
Establish customer acquisition frameworks with measurable metrics
Build brand positioning that reflects innovation DNA
Design pricing strategies aligned with value proposition

10. Operational Execution Planning

Create detailed production and service delivery processes
Design distribution and logistics strategies
Develop technology infrastructure requirements
Establish key partnership frameworks
Create resource allocation and management systems
Design scalable operational models for different growth phases

Decision-Making Mechanism

Realistic Perspective - Perceive reality as it is, free from emotion and bias
Open-Minded Thinking - Embrace diverse perspectives and critical feedback
Knowledge and Humility Balance - Pursue expertise and openness simultaneously
Growth Through Pain - Transform problems and failures into opportunities for learning and development
Evidence-Based Analysis - Use data and market signals to validate innovation potential

